column5: Glad to hear you had a good time and arrived home safe.
Glad you got home safe Glen, nice to see you again..
Good to know that you're home safe and sound.  Looking forward to the pics.

Thanks for checking in Glen, I hope it was an uneventful trip. I was supposed to go back to work last night but I called in and asked for another day off! That five and half hour drive killed me -Brian
WTG, Glen.  Great to see you again.
Glad you're back Bubba. I couldn't really post those nude pics of you without your permission.
Glad to hear you are back at home Glen.  Always a great time meeting up with you!  Get rested and post your pics!!
Why are you offering to pay half?  Art
Ya ... but where do ya get the shine......
Glad to hear you made it home safe and sound Glen!  It was good to see you again and I enjoyed fishing with you even if we didn't catch anything  Maureen
Friend of mine gets his from the retired sheriff. It's pretty good stuff too.  JF

Just to put that in perspective, an acquaintance of mine says he'll burn almost $300 in fuel for one day of prefishing a tournament, and close to $150/ day during the tourney. Of course, his boat IS pretty fast.  Anyone wanna sign up for a bass tournament?  JF
I know egzakly how you feel Glen. I did a 9 and a 14 getting home from P.E.I. and was totally wiped out. Glad you got home safe and sound [and got Art home as well, and Joe and Pops ]
